title: Alabama Homecoming 2015: See Big Al, Crimsonettes, Million Dollar Band, more from parade
text:
Comments 
TUSCALOOSA, Alabama -- Alabama fans gathered along University Boulevard for another jam-packed homecoming parade, featuring the likes of Big Al, the Crimsonettes, the Million Dollar Band and many more. 
Alabama gymnastics head coach Dana Duckworth served as the grand marshal, while the homecoming court including queen-elect Katelyn Katsafanas followed right behind. 
Dancers, drivers and other performers showcased their talents for a good 30 minutes or so, while the highlight may have been Mallet Assembly's hilarious and thoughtfully designed "Mad Max: Fury Road" motif, complete with a flamethrower guitar guy. 
See photos from the parade above.
